01:03:15,215 --> 01:03:16,204
...and a snake.

784
01:03:59,659 --> 01:04:02,457
I'm worried about the river, we swim.

785
01:04:06,099 --> 01:04:07,088
You never know, sir.

786
01:04:33,560 --> 01:04:36,791
I have, of course,
looked everywhere here already.

787
01:04:58,051 --> 01:04:59,575
Everything you do...

788
01:05:00,453 --> 01:05:03,013
...everything you say, write...

789
01:05:04,958 --> 01:05:06,550
...you do it superbly.

790
01:05:07,760 --> 01:05:09,990
And you're always going to, all your life...

791
01:05:10,263 --> 01:05:11,992
...whatever you turn your hand to. I know it.

792
01:05:15,468 --> 01:05:18,801
And I know you must feel
that I don't belong in your world.

793
01:05:19,973 --> 01:05:22,908
I don't.

794
01:06:22,902 --> 01:06:24,164
Between the soup and the baked beans.

795
01:06:24,904 --> 01:06:26,428
Thank you so much.

796
01:06:26,906 --> 01:06:28,897
I caught her before she got to the check-out.

797
01:06:29,409 --> 01:06:31,206
She's been gone for hours...

798
01:06:31,411 --> 01:06:32,537
..I thought I'd never see her again. Never.

799
01:06:34,213 --> 01:06:35,578
Well... all's well that...

800
01:06:35,949 --> 01:06:37,814
Please do, tell me your name?

801
01:06:40,720 --> 01:06:42,153
I'm Maurice, John.

802
01:06:44,590 --> 01:06:45,716
Iris' friend.

803
01:06:46,893 --> 01:06:48,724
I was a witness at your wedding.

804
01:06:51,364 --> 01:06:52,888
Well, I'm late for a meeting.

805
01:06:53,599 --> 01:06:57,057
-Maurice, so sorry...
-So sorry.

806
01:07:29,202 --> 01:07:31,727
Were you trying to get away from me?

807
01:07:33,573 --> 01:07:36,474
Did you want to leave me, Iris?

808
01:07:38,978 --> 01:07:40,639
Please?

809
01:07:55,874 --> 01:07:58,809
I feel as if I don't know anything about you.

810
01:07:59,144 --> 01:08:00,406
When you know
everything about me, then I'll be dead.

811
01:08:01,380 --> 01:08:02,677
He's a Professor of Ancient History..

812
01:08:03,115 --> 01:08:04,946
They have a maling influence on you I think.

813
01:08:05,217 --> 01:08:06,411
They all have, all your 'friends'.

814
01:08:06,785 --> 01:08:08,844
He's a teacher, a master of thought.

815
01:08:09,455 --> 01:08:11,616
You talk, do you. You master thoughts together?

816
01:08:12,291 --> 01:08:14,384
We make love, yes,
but that's not the important thing.

817
01:08:14,660 --> 01:08:16,059
Then he goes home to his wife in London.

818
01:08:16,829 --> 01:08:17,818
Does it frighten you?

819
01:08:18,363 --> 01:08:21,764
I feel as if I'm standing in a long line of suitors...

820
01:08:21,967 --> 01:08:23,127
...waiting for a kind word.

821
01:08:24,036 --> 01:08:25,060
I'll always give you a kind word.

822
01:08:26,138 --> 01:08:27,628
We must accept me as I am.

823
01:08:28,407 --> 01:08:30,568
And I'm to be kept in my box or not kept at all.

824
01:08:31,009 --> 01:08:33,807
Nothing matters except...

825
01:08:35,013 --> 01:08:36,344
...loving what is good.

826
01:08:36,782 --> 01:08:37,771
Am I good?

827
01:08:40,252 --> 01:08:42,117
Just...

828
01:08:42,421 --> 01:08:45,117
...keep tight hold of me and it'll be all right.

829
01:08:51,563 --> 01:08:54,031
Who are you with now, Iris?

830
01:08:54,066 --> 01:08:55,055
Who is it?

831
01:09:00,439 --> 01:09:04,034
We're lost.

832
01:09:05,377 --> 01:09:07,572
We're lost. We're lost...

833
01:09:17,589 --> 01:09:18,920
There is no reason for this.

834
01:09:19,224 --> 01:09:20,851
And if there is I don't know it.

835
01:09:21,794 --> 01:09:25,127
I hate you Iris. You stupid cow.

836
01:09:25,531 --> 01:09:26,964
I bloody loathe you.

837
01:09:27,266 --> 01:09:29,393
Every bloody inch of you.

838
01:09:29,902 --> 01:09:32,598
All your friends have finished with you.

839
01:09:33,005 --> 01:09:35,803
Nobody else has you anymore...

840
01:09:36,308 --> 01:09:40,972
...except your fucking best friend
Doctor fucking Alzheimer....

841
01:09:41,346 --> 01:09:43,974
...with all his fucking gifts.

842
01:09:44,449 --> 01:09:47,543
I've got you now and I don't want you.

843
01:09:48,854 --> 01:09:51,118
I've never known anything about you at all...

844
01:09:51,423 --> 01:09:52,890
...and now I don't care.

845
01:10:02,601 --> 01:10:03,693
I think it's time I told you about...

846
01:10:03,836 --> 01:10:04,825
...some of my friends...

847
01:10:05,904 --> 01:10:08,395
...the people in my past -- of my heart and...

848
01:10:09,241 --> 01:10:10,230
...and not.

849
01:10:12,778 --> 01:10:13,767
Oh dear.

850
01:10:21,253 --> 01:10:22,686
ought I to take notes?

851
01:10:30,529 --> 01:10:32,429
There was a friend who was a student with me.

852
01:10:34,700 --> 01:10:36,258
No, no, he can wait.

853
01:10:38,904 --> 01:10:40,895
He was not the first person I went to bed with...

854
01:10:41,773 --> 01:10:42,967
...that was Harry..

855
01:10:44,343 --> 01:10:46,971
then there was Roger,
who wanted to marry me...

856
01:10:47,779 --> 01:10:50,339
And Oscar
who said he couldn't live without me...

857
01:10:51,683 --> 01:10:53,150
...and Tom...

858
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:58,986
...who far too clearly could but...

859
01:10:59,291 --> 01:11:02,260
So, the student friend
I had resisted going to bed with...

860
01:11:04,129 --> 01:11:05,528
...joined the Army during the war....

861
01:11:05,831 --> 01:11:06,991
...and promptly asked me to marry him for...

862
01:11:08,800 --> 01:11:10,427
...he was certain he was going to be killed...

863
01:11:10,736 --> 01:11:12,101
..and wanted me to have the window's pension.

864
01:11:14,039 --> 01:11:15,301
Yes, I know they all said that.

865
01:11:16,975 --> 01:11:17,964
Anyway...

866
01:11:19,912 --> 01:11:21,311
...I didn't want to marry him...

867
01:11:23,315 --> 01:11:25,078
...but I did go to bed with him.

868
01:11:25,717 --> 01:11:29,949
...I thought that best before
he went off to fight, because you never know...

869
01:11:35,360 --> 01:11:37,089
...anyway, he, he was killed--

870
01:11:37,863 --> 01:11:39,262
--my student friend...

871
01:11:41,099 --> 01:11:42,498
...and we weren't married.

872
01:11:45,203 --> 01:11:46,465
So no pension.

873
01:11:54,780 --> 01:11:55,769
there.

874
01:11:55,981 --> 01:11:57,073
It wouldn't have been much anyway...

875
01:11:57,282 --> 01:11:58,681
I know, because I had friends killed.

876
01:11:59,017 --> 01:12:01,247
Their wives got very little, they get very little.

877
01:12:06,024 --> 01:12:08,356
Is that all? I mean, roughly?

878
01:12:10,662 --> 01:12:12,892
What about the 'friends' in your other world?

879
01:12:14,199 --> 01:12:15,666
You know more about me than anyone on earth.

880
01:12:20,005 --> 01:12:21,233
You are my world.

881
01:12:43,695 --> 01:12:44,684
Thank you.

882
01:12:46,465 --> 01:12:48,626
After all that I rather hoped it might be time...

883
01:12:48,967 --> 01:12:50,229
...for me to get my kind word.

884
01:12:56,942 --> 01:12:59,410
You don't need to do it on your own.
Vale House is very good.

885
01:13:00,379 --> 01:13:01,744
You're exhausted, you know that.

886
01:13:02,147 --> 01:13:04,081
Of course I am. It's something that we share.

887
01:13:04,483 --> 01:13:06,713
We're in a state of grace.

888
01:13:07,285 --> 01:13:08,946
I think we understand each other.

889
01:13:10,022 --> 01:13:11,046
What do you think?

890
01:13:12,090 --> 01:13:16,390
I don'tknow. There's always help if you need it.

891
01:13:17,562 --> 01:13:20,258
There isn't any help for her.

892
01:13:23,702 --> 01:13:24,691
What?

893
01:13:25,470 --> 01:13:27,461
Sorry? Sorry?

894
01:13:28,040 --> 01:13:29,234
Nothing.

895
01:13:38,583 --> 01:13:39,572
Why has Willie Thorne
got two rabbits tattooed on his bald head?

896
01:13:40,419 --> 01:13:42,910
I don't know, why has Willie Thorne
got two rabbits tattooed on his bald head?

897
01:13:43,488 --> 01:13:45,820
Cos from a distance they look like hares.

898
01:13:50,362 --> 01:13:51,556
Janet's dead, Iris.

899
01:13:56,568 --> 01:13:59,002
They want me to say a few words
but I can't think of any.

900
01:13:59,571 --> 01:14:01,937
Janet's dead, Iris.

901
01:14:12,684 --> 01:14:16,245
I miss Janet very much.

902
01:14:17,389 --> 01:14:21,792
I miss Janet because I used to store up...

903
01:14:22,227 --> 01:14:24,252
...funny things to tell her that happened to us.

904
01:14:26,231 --> 01:14:28,131
...things I can no longer tell Iris.

905
01:14:29,801 --> 01:14:31,996
Another friend visited us...

906
01:14:32,304 --> 01:14:33,464
...in Oxford overnight recently....

907
01:14:34,239 --> 01:14:36,469
...and I found her cleaning the bath.

908
01:14:37,742 --> 01:14:39,835
I said, "Oh, please, there's no need".

909
01:14:40,812 --> 01:14:42,905
She said, "Oh yes there is,
I want to take a bath".

910
01:14:48,019 --> 01:14:49,486
I was hoping to be able...

911
01:14:50,689 --> 01:14:52,054
...to tell Janet that story...

912
01:14:52,757 --> 01:14:54,782
...she would have enjoyed it.

913
01:14:55,827 --> 01:14:57,886
She would have...laughed.

914
01:15:00,499 --> 01:15:01,557
I mean, I think...

915
01:15:07,139 --> 01:15:10,233
...Anna Karenina, Tolstoy, you know...

916
01:15:10,509 --> 01:15:14,275
...when on her way to the station
to throw herself under a train...

917
01:15:15,180 --> 01:15:17,740
...sees something funny
which she thinks to tell Vronsky....

918
01:15:18,216 --> 01:15:19,205
...her lover, about...

919
01:15:19,784 --> 01:15:21,684
...we all do it, I do it with Iris...

920
01:15:22,020 --> 01:15:23,078
...and Janet, all our friends...

921
01:15:24,489 --> 01:15:29,483
...but, then Anna thought that
she wouldn't be seeing Vronsky again...

922
01:15:30,095 --> 01:15:32,325
...because she was about to kill herself.

923
01:15:36,835 --> 01:15:37,893
Oh, but, you don't want to hear this...

924
01:15:41,006 --> 01:15:43,304
...Janet didn't kill herself...

925
01:15:47,646 --> 01:15:52,015
But, if there's one thing
that would have prevented...

926
01:15:53,018 --> 01:15:55,919
...Anna from throwing herself under a train...

927
01:15:56,755 --> 01:16:01,692
...that would be it,
the thought of telling something funny...

928
01:16:03,361 --> 01:16:05,352
...to the man she loves.

929
01:16:09,534 --> 01:16:11,263
The love is over...

930
01:16:15,507 --> 01:16:18,874
...though...

931
01:16:21,179 --> 01:16:22,840
...life will...

932
01:16:24,282 --> 01:16:25,874
...soon be over.

933
01:16:28,286 --> 01:16:29,275
That's all.

934
01:16:31,223 --> 01:16:33,248
Goodbye, Janet.

935
01:16:33,792 --> 01:16:35,817
No, no, Janet. Jan!

936
01:16:36,528 --> 01:16:38,257
It's all right, Iris.

937
01:16:50,008 --> 01:16:50,997
Wrong, wrong, wrong.

938
01:16:51,243 --> 01:16:52,540
-Wrong driving.
Stop it, Iris!

939
01:16:52,911 --> 01:16:53,900
Wrong driving!

940
01:16:54,045 --> 01:16:55,034
No. Stop it, Iris.

941
01:16:55,380 --> 01:16:59,339
-Not house. Not mother..
-Iris, it's very dangerous.

942
01:16:59,618 --> 01:17:03,281
Them! Them!

943
01:17:06,024 --> 01:17:07,048
Iris!

944
01:17:13,865 --> 01:17:14,854
Puss.

945
01:17:17,102 --> 01:17:19,832
My old mouse -- My old cat mouse.

946
01:17:20,438 --> 01:17:21,427
Where are you?

947
01:17:49,567 --> 01:17:51,501
I...

948
01:17:54,472 --> 01:17:56,269
...love...

949
01:17:58,209 --> 01:17:59,335
...you.

950
01:18:01,379 --> 01:18:07,340
Ah, little mouse. I know you do.

951
01:18:22,734 --> 01:18:24,065
I used to be...

952
01:18:24,969 --> 01:18:27,563
...so afraid of being alone with you...

953
01:18:28,340 --> 01:18:30,035
...now I can't be without you.

954
01:18:39,851 --> 01:18:41,910
Let's get us -- home...

955
01:18:43,188 --> 01:18:45,486
...and then there'll be tomorrow...

956
01:18:47,292 --> 01:18:48,987
...and the nex tday...

957
01:18:50,295 --> 01:18:51,387
...and the next...

958
01:18:52,163 --> 01:18:53,494
...and on we go...

959
01:18:55,834 --> 01:19:00,100
...getting closer and closest together...

960
01:19:02,741 --> 01:19:03,730
Oh, your ring.

961
01:19:05,043 --> 01:19:06,476
It's so worn now.

962
01:19:06,811 --> 01:19:07,800
Where did you get it?

963
01:19:08,012 --> 01:19:09,001
From a pawnbrokers.

964
01:19:10,682 --> 01:19:12,047
I like things that are worn down.

965
01:19:14,085 --> 01:19:16,349
Which wear and wear and wear...

966
01:19:19,457 --> 01:19:20,754
...until they go.

967
01:19:38,777 --> 01:19:39,869
We've had a bit of luck.

968
01:19:40,812 --> 01:19:42,905
Usual thing, I'm afraid -- Somebody's died.

969
01:19:45,417 --> 01:19:46,406
Iris...

970
01:19:47,218 --> 01:19:50,187
...don't you have a smile for Doctor Gudgeon?

971
01:19:51,356 --> 01:19:52,345
No?

972
01:19:55,794 --> 01:19:56,783
No.

973
01:19:57,395 --> 01:19:59,920
So -- the time has come.

974
01:20:02,867 --> 01:20:04,300
You know it would, Professor Bayley.

975
01:20:05,136 --> 01:20:06,125
Yes.

976
01:20:07,038 --> 01:20:09,666
She didn't have a smile for you today.

977
01:20:10,341 --> 01:20:13,538
Yes. Well, we must make a start.

978
01:20:15,046 --> 01:20:16,877
-What do I do?
-Nothing any more.

979
01:20:20,585 --> 01:20:22,553
Vale House is a very friendly place, you know.

980
01:20:24,122 --> 01:20:25,384
I was, surpr....

981
01:20:27,225 --> 01:20:28,590
...I mean, this is one of the best.

982
01:20:31,329 --> 01:20:34,560
More difficult to get into than...well, Eton.

983
01:21:15,707 --> 01:21:17,800
-Taxi for Vale House?
-Yes.

984
01:21:19,511 --> 01:21:21,536
Lady's on the stairs, but I can't get her down.

985
01:21:23,281 --> 01:21:24,270
Shall I?

986
01:21:30,788 --> 01:21:33,348
You all right, my love?

987
01:21:35,593 --> 01:21:36,958
We're going for a little drive.

988
01:21:39,531 --> 01:21:40,520
What's your name then?

989
01:21:45,570 --> 01:21:46,559
Iris.

990
01:21:48,907 --> 01:21:50,704
Yes, it's Iris.

991
01:21:52,010 --> 01:21:53,034
All right then, Iris...

992
01:21:54,078 --> 01:21:55,636
...you'll be all right, my love, come on.

993
01:21:55,680 --> 01:21:56,669
Come on, upsy-daisy.

994
01:22:03,421 --> 01:22:04,410
There you go.

995
01:22:05,123 --> 01:22:06,988
Lovely.

996
01:22:33,952 --> 01:22:35,510
Human beings love each...

997
01:22:36,287 --> 01:22:38,221
...in sex -- in friendship...

998
01:22:39,090 --> 01:22:40,853
...and when they're in love.

999
01:22:42,226 --> 01:22:43,955
And they cherish other beings...

1000
01:22:44,729 --> 01:22:47,755
...humans -- animals, plants...

1001
01:22:49,567 --> 01:22:50,761
...even stones.

1002
01:22:51,502 --> 01:22:53,561
She'll be fine now, won't you Iris?

1003
01:22:56,207 --> 01:22:57,936
You can visit any time you like...

1004
01:22:58,309 --> 01:22:59,674
...come all day if you want to.

1005
01:23:04,916 --> 01:23:06,577
Stay the night, that's all right...

1006
01:23:07,185 --> 01:23:09,346
...we can make arrangements
for you to do that anytime.

1007
01:24:05,276 --> 01:24:07,176
It was so quiet...

1008
01:24:10,348 --> 01:24:11,474
...when she died.

1009
01:24:14,252 --> 01:24:18,052
Do you know,
I thought I wouldn't mind doing that myself..

1010
01:24:20,758 --> 01:24:24,023
I had a joke to tell her.

1011
01:24:26,597 --> 01:24:30,658
It wasn't a very good one
but she'd have laughed.

1012
01:24:32,136 --> 01:24:33,865
We need to believe in something divine.

1013
01:24:34,639 --> 01:24:35,901
Without the need for God.

1014
01:24:37,442 --> 01:24:40,036
Something we might call love...

1015
01:24:40,545 --> 01:24:41,534
...or goodness.

1016
01:24:42,980 --> 01:24:44,106
As the psalm says...

1017
01:24:45,383 --> 01:24:47,146
..."Whither shall I go from thy spirit...

1018
01:24:48,119 --> 01:24:49,848
...whither shall I flee from thy presence?

1019
01:24:51,589 --> 01:24:53,648
If I ascend unto Heaven thou art there...

1020
01:24:54,692 --> 01:24:57,422
...if I make my bed in Hell behold thou art there.

1021
01:24:59,130 --> 01:25:00,722
If I take the wings of the morning...

1022
01:25:01,165 --> 01:25:02,894
...and dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea...

1023
01:25:04,435 --> 01:25:06,494
...even there shall thy hand lead me...

1024
01:25:07,605 --> 01:25:09,573
...and thy right hand shall hold me."

